Ruby programmer? It’s easy to use this data in your own app! Use the gem like this: 

require 'everypolitician'
country = Everypolitician::Index.new.country('France')
house = country.legislature('National-Assembly')
house.popolo.terms.find_by(id: 'term/12').memberships.each do |membership|
  puts "#{membership.person.name} (#{membership.party.name}): #{membership.person.gender}"
end

Libraries also available in Python and PHP.

Main Sources: http://www.nosdeputes.fr/, http://www.assemblee-nationale.fr, https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Catégorie:Député_de_la_XIVe_législature_de_la_Ve_République, http://gender-balance.org/
